{"/service/ndnp/au/batch_au_dean_ver01/data/sn85038485/00340583000/1920112301/0481.xml":{"full_text":"PARTIAI1V THROWN\nOFF STOCK LIST\nImprovements Extended Two\nto Ten Points In Many Is\nsues In Face of\nUnsettlement\nBy Associated Press\nNew York, November 22.\u2014In the\nvernacular of the speculative element,\nthe -stock market today \"turned the\ncorner,\" the list almost as a whole\nmanifesting an unmistakable disposi\ntion to throw off the acute depression\nof the last three weeks.\nThis improvement, extending from\ntwo to almost ten points in many is\nsues. was accomplished in the face of\nrenewed unsettlement in other mar\nkets for leading staples, notably grains\nand other food stuffs.\nEvents over the Sunday recess were\nmainly helpful to the recovery ofc\n^tocks. Local federal reserves strength\nened. call money dropping to 5 per ent,\nthe lowest quotation In many months,\nafter ope'ning at 7 per cent and gen\nerally believed that many impaired ac\ncounts had been \"taken over\" by\nstrong interests at private settlement.\nEorei\u00a9 i exchange also indicated\nfirmer conditions abroad, although\nLondon reported further distrust over\nthe outlook for commodities and con\ntraction in trading in securities grow\ning out of the situation in Gr \u20183ce.\nIndustrial developments at home, es\npecially in the west and southwest,\npointed to continued retrenchment, this\nbeing evidenced by the additional de\ncrease in tonnage on leading railway\nsystems running out of Chicago and\nSt. Louis. As was to be expected, to\nday's greatest gains \\vere made oy is\nsues of recent weakness in the steel,\nequipirftnt, oil and shipping divisions.\nThe more conspicuous gains included\ncrucible steel. NTsc; Mexican pe\npeu^leum, S^c: Panama petroleum,\nft\u2019/ic; Baldwin locomotive, 4Vic; Amer\nh:ap locomotive, 3c; retail stroes, fc:\ntobacco products, 5\u2018sc. and Reading,\n\"V2C. Other gains amnog rails es\npecial ties extended from 3 to 5 points.\nSales amounted to 1.100,000 shares.\nConvertible railway bonds benefited\nchiefly by the rjsp in stocks and liberty\nissues, also closed at gains. Total sales,\npar value, were $13,850,000.\nOld United States bonds were un\nchanged on call.\nNew York Stocks\nBy Associated i*re\u2014\nSales High. Low Cl.*se\nAm. Beet Sugar 1200 55%\nAmerican Can 4200 26\n51\n24\nAm. Car F... 6200 124 122\nAm. H. L., pfd 5000\nAm. Inter. Corp. 116\n\u25a0Am. Loco. 7000\nAm. Ian seed 1900\n47%\n46*\n85\n54\nAm. Sm. lief. 6300 451\no\n07%\n74\n99 y2\n66%\n42\n46%\n4;>l\u00bb\n81\n51\n4 4\n93%\n70%\n99\n64\n38\nAmerican Sugar 7500\nAm. Sum. Tob. 2300\nAm. Tel. Sc Tel. 1600\nAmer. Woolen. 3000\nAnaconda Cop. 8500\nAtchison 4000\nAll. Coast Line 500\nAtl. G. W. I. 5100 111% 108\nBaldwin Loco.. 331\nBalt. Ohio.. 5300 40\nt*eVh. Steel *\u2018B\u201d 262 67\n86% 84%\n89 8S%\n98%\n94\n38\n3%\n26\n124\n4 7 V,\n45%\n84%\n54\n45%\n97 >4\n74%\n99%\n0 4%\n41%\n86%\n89\n111%\n98\n40\nCanadian Pac. 5600 118% 116% 1181\nCentral Leather 3000\nChandler Motors 4000\nChes. Sc Ohio. 5000\nChi. M. &.St.fP. 3600\nCM,, R. I. P. 5200\nChino Copper.. 4300\nCoca-Cola 1800\nCol. Fuel Iron 300\nCorn Products 196\nCrucible Steel. 217\nCuba Cane Sug. 3000\nlJrio 6400\nGen. Klee.\nGen. Motors 705\nGt. North.', pfd 6 400\nGulf Sts. Steel 1500\n39\n77\n65\n36\n3i\n2.1\n24\n28%\n74\n96%\n31\n16%\n38\n74%\n63%\n34%\n30%\n19%\n22%\n28%\n71\n88\n31%\n16\n39\n64%\n36\n31\n21%\n24\n28%\n74\n95\n31\n10%\n7200 126 122% 120%\n35% 14%\nlb. Central\n81\n37\n200 89\nInspiration Cop. 2400\nInt. M. M., pfd. 6100\nlitter Paper 3400\nKennecott Cop. 5000\n50%\n20%\nT8%\n34%\n89\n33%\n52\n47\n19%\n81\n37\nS3\n35\n5S%\n50%\n20%\nL Sc N.101\n313 163\n2000\n4600\n7400\n17%\n12%\n3 4\n6300 23%\n4200 77%\n600 26%\n000 100\nII\n88%\n3%\n79%\n41\n4000\n286\n300\n7700\n35\n11%\n89%\n80\nMex. Petroleum\nMiami Copper..\nMid. Sts. Oil..\nMidvale Steel\nMo Pacific\nN Y. Central..\nN. Y., N. ty.\nHartford\nNor. S- West.\nNor. Pacific\nok la. Pr. Sc lief. 3300\nI\u20